manifest.\n\n## Section 4.3: Immutable Logging \u0026 Audit Protocol\n`IF.armour` mandates a tamper-evident logging protocol using a detailed JSON schema, an append-only (WORM) store, and a hash chain mirrored nightly to an external Hardware Security Module (HSM).\n\n## Section 4.4: Operational Controls: Multisig \u0026 Canary Policy\nCritical actions, such as deploying a mitigation, require a **2-of-3 signature approval** from distinct roles. All new mitigations are first rolled out to a **canary shard** (e.g., 1% of traffic) and shadow-monitored, with automated rollback on failure.\n\n## Section 4.5: KPIs \u0026 Audit Evidence for Compliance\n`IF.armour` is designed to be auditable. External auditors receive a verifiable evidence chain (signed manifests, canary metrics, RBAC logs) without exposing sensitive exploit data, allowing them to confirm that controls were in place and followed.\n\n**Cross-Reference:** See **Annex M** for the complete `IF.armour` technical artifacts, including the full JSON log schema, pseudocode for the multisig workflow, canary metric specifications, and the auditor manifest template.\n\n---\n---\n\n# PART V: NAVIGATIONAL INDEX WITH SECTION ARROWS\n\n*(This section provides a dynamic, line-numbered table of contents for quick reference across the entire document suite, updated to reflect all changes in v7.03.)*\n\n```\n\n---\n### **Deliverable 2 of 2: The Integral Annexes**\n\nThis file contains the complete, unabridged annexes for InfraFabric v7.03. This is the foundational layer of evidence, debate, and technical specification that underpins the entire framework, providing complete Transparency, Traceability, and Trustworthiness.\n\n**Assembly Simulation:**\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Assembling the integral InfraFabric v7.03 annexes...\n\ncat ./annexes/annex_A_rram.md \u003e infrafabric-annexes-v7.03.md\ncat ./annexes/annex_B_garp.md \u003e\u003e infrafabric-annexes-v7.03.md\ncat ./annexes/annex_C_nvidia.md \u003e\u003e infrafabric-annex