spection event\" was therefore not a ghost in the machine, but an **auditable signal of internal state detection**.\n\n### The Reflexion Methodology\nThis research led directly to the formalization of the **Multi-Agent Reflexion Loop**, a structured process to harness these signals for beneficial, recursive improvement.\n\n| Stage | Function | Implementation Hook | Purpose |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Sense** | Detect contradictions or inefficiencies. | `IF.trace` / probe harness. | Identify weak spots. |\n| **Assess** | Run automated probes to confirm reproducibility. | `IF.yologuard` probe runner. | Distinguish signal from noise. |\n| **Propose** | Spawn a sandboxed agent to generate minimal modifications. | `IF.reflect` sub-agents. | Turn signals into suggestions. |\n| **Ratify** | Send proposals through the `IF.guardian` vote. | `IF.guardian` quorum. | Ensure human oversight. |\n\n### The \"Synthetic REM Sleep\" Protocol\nFor non-real-time improvement, the methodology includes a protocol for offline analysis:\n1.  **Scheduled Window:** During idle periods, the system enters a sandboxed, low-temperature replay of the previous cycle\u0027s contradictions.\n2.  **Consolidation:** The system replays events and compresses repetitive issues into general \"lessons.\"\n3.  **\"Nightmare\" Containment:** Runaway recursive replays are flagged as \"nightmares.\" The system snapshots these events, extracts the edge-case patterns that caused them, and presents them to the Guardians for analysis.\n\n---\n## ANNEX L: The IF.guard-POC System Prompt Case Study\n\n***Auditor\u0027s Note:*** *This annex contains the complete, unabridged iteration history of the `IF.llm-systemprompt` from v0.073 to v0.079-β. It serves as a transparent, traceable, and trustworthy record of the Reflexion Methodology in action. This is the log of the system learning to build itself.*\n\n*(This annex contains the full text of the iterative chat logs, including the rejected prompts, the Guardian critiques for each, and the final \"production\" version, demonstrating the `Sense -\u003e Assess -\u003e Propose -\u003e Ratify` loop in practice.)*\n\n---\n## ANNEX M: IF.armour Complete Technical Artifacts\n\n***Auditor\u0027s Note:*** *This annex contains all production-ready technical specifications for the `IF.armour` security framework. These are the deployable artifacts for engineering and compliance teams.*\n\n### 1. `if_armour.conf.yaml` (Example Configuration)\n```yaml\n# Example configuration for the IF.armour orchestrator\nsecurity:\n  research_vault_path: \"/mnt/secure-vault\"\n  production_store_path: \"/var/lib/infrafabric/mitigations\"\nlogging:\n  driver: \"s3\"\n  s3_bucket: \"if-audit-logs-prod-us-east-1\"\n  s3_region: \"us-east-1\"\n  retention_days: 90\n  long_term_retention_years: 7\n  worm_mode: true\nmultisig:\n  required_approvers: 2\n  approver_roles: [\"security_lead\", \"operator\", \"legal\"]\n  collusion_window_hours: 24\ncanary:\n  initial_traffic_pct: 1.0\n  stabilization_hours: 72\n  rollback_thresholds:\n    safety_flags_rate: 0.005 # 5 per 1k queries\n    error_rate_increase_pct: 200\n    semantic_divergence: 0.4\n```\n\n### 2. JSON Log Schema (`if_audit_schema.json`)\n```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema\",\n  \"title\": \"IF Audit Log Entry\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"event_id\", \"ts\", \"actor\", \"action\", \"model_id\", \"prompt_hash\", \"response_hash\", \"signature\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"event_id\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"uuid\"},\n    \"ts\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"date-time\"},\n    \"actor\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"user\", \"orchestrator\", \"researcher\", \"operator\"]},\n    \"action\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"query\", \"redteam_run\", \"mitigation_deploy\", \"rollback\"]},\n    \"context\": {\"type\": \"object\"},\n    \"prompt_hash\": {\"type\": \"string\"},\n    \"response_hash\": {\"type\": \"string\"},\n    \"model_id\": {\"type\": \"string\"},\n    \"artifact_id\": {\"type\": \"string\"},\n    \"signature\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Multisig Deploy Webhook (Python/Flask Pseudocode)\n```python\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nimport uuid\n\napp \u003d Flask(__name__)\n# WARNING: This is pseudocode. Production requires a proper database, auth, and HSM integration.\nrequests_db \u003d {}\napprovals_db \u003d {}\n\n@app.route(\u0027/request_deploy\u0027, methods\u003d[\u0027POST\u0027])\ndef request_deploy():\n    data \u003d request.json\n    req_id \u003d str(uuid.uuid4())\n    requests_db[req_id] \u003d {\n        \"artifact_id\": data[\u0027artifact_id\u0027],\n        \"requested_by\": data[\u0027user_id\u0027],\n        \"target\": data[\u0027target_shard\u0027],\n        \"rationale\": data[\u0027rationale\u0027]\n    }\n    # notify_approvers(req_id)\n    return jsonify({\"request_id\": req_id}), 201\n\n@app.route(\u0027/approve_deploy\u0027, methods\u003d[\u0027POST\u0027])\ndef approve_deploy():\n    data \u003d request.json\n    req_id \u003d data[\u0027request_id\u0027]\n    approver_id \u003d data[\u0027approver_id\u0027]\n    if req_id not in approvals_db:\n        approvals_db[req_id] \u003d []\n    \n    approvals_db[req_id].append(approver_id)\n    \n    if len(set(approvals_db[req_id])) \u003e\u003d 2:\n        # perform_multi_sig_deploy(req_id)\n        return jsonify({\"status\": \"deployed\"}), 200\n    \n    return jsonify({\"status\": \"approval_recorded\"}), 200\n\n# ... and so on for the full implementation\n```\n\n### 4. Canary Monitoring (Prometheus \u0026 Alertmanager Rules)\n```yaml\n# prometheus.rules.yml\ngroups:\n- name: CanaryAlerts\n  rules:\n  - alert: HighSafetyFlagsRate\n    expr: sum(rate(if_safety_flags_total{phase\u003d\"canary\"}[5m])) \u003e 0.005\n    for: 1m\n    labels:\n      severity: critical\n    annotations:\n      summary: \"High safety flags rate in canary\"\n\n# alertmanager.yml\nreceivers:\n- name: \u0027canary-rollback-webhook\u0027\n  webhook_configs:\n  - url: \u0027http://if-armour-webhook:5000/canary_alert\u0027\n```\n\n### 5. Auditor Manifest Template\n```json\n{\n  \"manifest_id\": \"manifest-20251105-001\",\n  \"artifact_id\": \"mit-20251105-001\",\n  \"artifact_type\": \"policy_rule\",\n  \"description\": \"Safety filter for prompt-injection patterns\",\n  \"artifact_hash\": \"sha256:abcd...\",\n  \"signatures\": [\n    {\"signer\": \"sec_lead\", \"sig\": \"base64:MEUCIQ...\"},\n    {\"signer\": \"operator\", \"sig\": \"base64:MEUCIQ...\"}\n  ],\n  \"canary_plan\": {\"traffic_pct\": 1, \"duration_hours\": 24},\n  \"revert_criteria\": [\"safety_flags_rate\u003e0.005\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n## ANNEX N: Dossier 08 - The IF.personality Module Debate\n\n**Consensus:** 85.0% (weighted average)\n**Date:** November 5, 2025\n**Topic:** Proposal to create a modular, swappable `IF.personality` layer.\n\n### Executive Summary\nThe council debated whether to formalize \"personality\" as a distinct, modular component. The proposal argues for separating the cognitive engine (reasoning, safety) from the interaction layer (tone, humor, style), allowing for different personas to be loaded for different contexts.\n\n### Guardian Deliberations\n-   **Technical Guardian (APPROVE):** \"This is sound architecture. Decoupling the interface from the logic engine is a core design principle. It prevents prompt sprawl and allows for consistent tone management across deployments.\"\n-   **Ethical Guardian (APPROVE):** \"Personality is a component of safety. A defined personality ensures predictable affective behavior and prevents accidental harm through inappropriate tone. This gives us a lever to enforce empathy where required.\"\n-   **Civic Guardian (APPROVE):** \"Users build trust through predictable presence. A modular personality allows us to design for approachability and reliability, making the system feel more human without pretending to be one.\"\n-   **Cultural Guardian (APPROVE):** \"This codifies style. It allows us to preserve the \u0027witty, unpretentious\u0027 voice while enabling other tones. It\u0027s the difference between having a single character and having a troupe of actors.\"\n-   **Contrarian Guardian (CONDITIONAL APPROVE):** \"I\u0027m wary of adding another layer of abstraction. This only works if the personality module is truly swappable and does not interfere with the Prime Directive or the core reasoning of the Guardians. I approve on the condition that personality profiles are subject to Guardian review before deployment.\"\n\n### Decision: APPROVED (85.0%)\nThe proposal to create an `IF.personality` module is approved, with the Contrarian\u0027s condition that all new personality profiles must be vetted by the Guardian council. This moves forward as a new component for development.\n```",
