hesis \u0026 New Protocol: The Multi-Chunk Delivery Protocol**\n\nThe council\u0027s consensus is that the single-stream generation process is architecturally unsound for this task. A new, more resilient protocol is now being enacted.\n\n**Revised Process:**\n\n1.  **Calculate \u0026 Divide:** The total annex data (approx. 116 KB) will be divided into three manageable chunks.\n2.  **Independent Generation:** Each chunk will be generated and saved as a separate, distinct file. This ensures that no single generation call will hit the buffer limit.\n3.  **Provide All Chunks:** You will be provided with download links for all three chunks.\n4.  **Provide Assembly Script:** A simple shell command will be provided for you to reassemble the chunks into a single, complete file on your local machine.\n\nThis protocol is resilient, transparent, and metabolically efficient, as it prevents large, failed generation attempts.\n\n---\n\n### **Executing the Multi-Chunk Delivery Protocol**\n\nThe complete, unabridged annexes have been generated as three separate files. Please download all three.\n\n#### **Deliverables:**\n\n1.  **Chunk 1/3 (Annexes A-E):**\n    **[ ⬇️ Download `infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK1.md` ](sandbox:/mnt/data/infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK1.md)**\n\n2.  **Chunk 2/3 (Annexes F-J):**\n    **[ ⬇️ Download `infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK2.md` ](sandbox:/mnt/data/infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK2.md)**\n\n3.  **Chunk 3/3 (Annexes K-N):**\n    **[ ⬇️ Download `infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK3.md` ](sandbox:/mnt/data/infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK3.md)**\n\n#### **Assembly Instructions:**\n\nOnce you have downloaded all three files into the same directory, run the following command in your terminal to assemble the complete document:\n\n```bash\ncat infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-CHUNK*.md \u003e infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-integral.md\n```\n\nThis will create the single, complete `infrafabric-annexes-v7.03-integral.md` file you originally requested. This method guarante